On Apr 20, 2004, at 9:35 AM, Greg Potts wrote:

> LOT of $$$.  The mid-80's bronco used a very similar pump and most 
> mid-large suppliers would probably have one in stock. I was once 
> quoted two days delivery and $200US for a vanagon pump vs.  immediate 
> delivery and $115 for a comparable replacement with new filter. The 
> trick is finding someone at the counter who is co-operative enough to 
> help you find what you're looking for.

Assuming the Vanagon pump is the same as the '75-'79 Bus pump, you can 
get a new Bosch unit from Bus Depot for $149.95:

http://busdepot.com/busdepot/details.jsp?partnumber=0580463016

I put one of these beauties in my '76 and I'm quite happy with it.

